---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service for CordIQ custom Discord bot development services."
  updated="July 20, 2026"
>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      CordIQ ("we", "us") provides custom Discord bot development, hosting and
      maintenance services. By ordering a project or using our website
      (cordiq.xyz) or Discord server, you agree to these terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. How orders work</h2>
    <p>
      Projects are scoped through a consultation on our Discord server. Work
      begins only after we both agree in writing (in your ticket) on scope,
      price and timeline. The agreed ticket conversation forms the project
      agreement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Payments</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Prices are quoted per project; "starting at" prices on the website are indicative, not binding quotes.</li>
      <li>Payment terms (deposit, milestones, or full payment) are agreed per project before work begins.</li>
      <li>Hosting and maintenance plans are billed on a recurring basis and can be cancelled anytime, effective at the end of the current billing period.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Delivery, revisions & refunds</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Delivery timelines are estimates agreed in your quote; we will notify you promptly of any delay.</li>
      <li>Each project includes the revision rounds specified in its quote, plus free fixes for bugs in delivered functionality.</li>
      <li>If we fail to deliver the agreed scope, you are entitled to a refund for the undelivered portion. Completed and accepted work is non-refundable.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      Upon full payment, ownership of the custom code written for your project
      transfers to you, excluding third-party libraries (which remain under
      their own licenses) and our pre-existing internal tooling, for which you
      receive a perpetual license to use within your project.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>6. Your responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You must comply with Discord's Terms of Service and Developer Policy in how you use any bot we build.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for the content and conduct of your own server and community.</li>
      <li>We will not build bots intended for spam, harassment, scams, data harvesting or any activity that violates Discord's policies or applicable law.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>7. Warranties & liability</h2>
    <p>
      Services are provided with professional skill and care. To the maximum
      extent permitted by law, our total liability for any claim is limited to
      the amount you paid for the specific project giving rise to the claim. We
      are not liable for indirect damages, lost profits, or actions taken by
      Discord Inc. against your server or account.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>8. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms; material changes will be announced on our
      Discord server. Continued use of our services after changes means you
      accept the updated terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms:
      <a href="mailto:contact@cordiq.xyz" class="text-brand-300 hover:underline">contact@cordiq.xyz</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="text-xs text-mist-500">
    CordIQ is an independent service and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or
    sponsored by Discord Inc.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
